                     <hi rend="largeCaps">ELIZABETH BRYANT</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390916-2503-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390916-2503-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390916-2503-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>for stealing, on the <rs id="t18390916-cd-98" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390916-2503-offence-1 t18390916-cd-98"></join>20th of August</rs>, 1 petticoat, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18390916-name-568" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-568" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-568" type="surname" value="SOWERBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-568" type="given" value="THOMAS BENJAMIN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390916-2503-offence-1 t18390916-name-568"></join>Thomas Benjamin Sowerby</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-569" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-569" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-569" type="surname" value="BILLSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-569" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY BILLSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in tie service of Thomas Benjamin Sowerby, a pawnbroker, in Chiswell-street. I know the prisoner by coming to our shop before—on the 20th of August she came—I watched her—this pet<lb></lb>ticoat was pinned up in the shop—she unpinned it, and when she saw I was watching her, she threw it into a customer's basket—I charged her with stealing it—she said she knew nothing about it, that it fell into the customer's basket as he passed by, but he was in the shop before the prisoner came in—she said if we had let her take it out of the shop and found it on her, we might have said she stole it, but as it was, we could not do any thing with her—I gave her in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-570" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-570" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-570" type="surname" value="COTTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-570" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS COTTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I took the prisoner into cus<lb></lb>tody—she said she knew nothing at all about it, that it fell on the man's basket as he passed by with it on his head.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">Property produced and sworn to.</hi>)</p>
